{{#> marketing}}
  {{#*inline "html-head-block"}}
    <title>Privacy Policy | AtlasArc</title>
    <meta name="description" content="AtlasArc privacy policy.">
    <meta property="og:title" content="AtlasArc Privacy Policy">
    <meta property="og:description" content="AtlasArc privacy policy.">
  {{/inline}}
  {{#*inline "body-block"}}
    <section class="page-hero container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">AtlasArc collects minimal data. The plugin collects none at all.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="band container legal-body">
      <article class="legal-doc">
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: July 2026</p>

        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Seamra Works ("we", "us") handles personal data in
        connection with the AtlasArc IntelliJ plugin and this website. AtlasArc is developed
        and published by Seamra Works. Seamra Works is the data controller under the General
        Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>

        <h2>1. The plugin</h2>
        <p>The AtlasArc plugin operates entirely on your local device. It reads your project's
        source code to compute architectural metrics and renders the results inside your IDE.
        <strong>No source code, metrics, project data, or personal information is ever
        transmitted to us or any third party.</strong> We have no visibility into how you use
        the plugin or what projects you analyse.</p>

        <h2>2. This website</h2>
        <p>This website uses Plausible Analytics to understand aggregate usage such as page
        views, referrers, approximate country, device type, and clicks on links to the
        JetBrains Marketplace. Plausible is configured without cookies and does not track
        visitors across websites. We do not run advertising networks, cross-site tracking
        scripts, or collect personal information through website analytics.</p>

        <h2>3. Purchases and subscriptions</h2>
        <p>Licences are sold through the
        <a
          href="{{marketplaceHref "privacy_marketplace"}}"
          data-analytics-cta="privacy_marketplace"
          data-analytics-destination="jetbrains_marketplace"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">JetBrains Marketplace</a>.
        All payment processing, subscription management, and related personal data (name,
        email, billing details) are handled by JetBrains s.r.o. under their own
        <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/legal/docs/privacy/privacy/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy Policy</a>.
        Seamra Works receives only the anonymised licence metadata necessary to validate your
        subscription.</p>

        <h2>4. Support contact</h2>
        <p>If you contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@atlasarc.io">support@atlasarc.io</a>, we receive and store
        your email address and the contents of your message. We use this information solely
        to respond to your enquiry. The legal basis is our legitimate interest in providing
        customer support (Article 6(1)(f) GDPR). We retain support correspondence for up to
        two years, after which it is deleted.</p>

        <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
        <p>Under GDPR you have the right to access, correct, or erase personal data we hold
        about you, to restrict or object to its processing, and to data portability. To
        exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@atlasarc.io">support@atlasarc.io</a>. You also have the
        right to lodge a complaint with the Dutch data protection authority
        (<a href="https://www.autoriteitpersoonsgegevens.nl" rel="noopener noreferrer">Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens</a>).</p>

        <h2>6. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy when our website, analytics setup, or other data
        practices change. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most
        recent revision. Continued use of the website or plugin after a change constitutes
        acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Data protection enquiries:
        <a href="mailto:support@atlasarc.io">support@atlasarc.io</a>.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  {{/inline}}
{{/marketing}}
